load_path_categories(25.10)                        load_path_categories(25.10)

Name
       load_path_categories - Loads the path category file in the Timing Debug
       form

Syntax
       load_path_categories

       [-help]

       -filename <filename>

       Loads  the  path category file in the Timing Debug form. The path cate-
       gory file contains category definitions that you saved  in  an  earlier
       timing debug analysis. To save path categories, use the save_path_cate-
       gories command.

       For  more information, see the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User
       Guide.

       Note: Before loading the path category file, make sure  that  the  path
       category name mentioned in the file does not exist in the existing path
       category list of the debugging session. To overwrite the existing cate-
       gories,  use the create_path_category -overwrite parameter for the path
       category file.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each load_path_categories parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man load_path_categories

       -filename <filename>
              Specifies the name of the category file.

Example
       The following command loads the path category file category.cat:

       load_path_categories -filename category.cat

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

